The paper discusses a visualization technique for data analysis, which involves arranging data instances into two-dimensional grids while preserving pairwise distances among the instances. This falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) since these fields often involve data analysis and visualization. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of binary space partitioning, which is a common technique in computational geometry (cs.CG) and spatial information systems (cs.SI).
